üëçüèª new design The revamped design looks fabulous; much better than the old one! 
As per one of the below reviews, it is not a good experience to receive an email the following day after payment is made informing that one of the items is out of stock. We hope the inventory system has been upgraded to prevent this again. It‚Äôd be ideal if there‚Äôs an option we could be notified via SMS or email when stock is available.
I‚Äôll review the revamped app for a bit more to decide if I want to change my rating to 5stars.

Poor service Many times.  Nobody informed ‚ÄòOut of stock‚Äô on the items that I ordered.  Although The order that will be sent to me show the stock item.  I Always have to call to check after their deliveries.
Today,  email and text message show my order is on the way.   After a Long wait, I called and found out my order had been cancelled due to some technical issue.   Nobody in Fairprice bother to call and inform.  I had been waiting for the order as one of the item I ordered urgently need to used.    Only a simply apologise and ask me to order again and they can only deliver the earliest that is next Monday!
I spent $500 to S$600 a month in Fairprice and what I get in return is many disappointment.
Leaving me no choice but to turn other supermart to buy my things.

Latest New Design Not User Friendly The new design is not intuitive to users.
It also doesn‚Äôt carry all the different categories of offers that are in the Straits Times, and these used to be in the old design of the app. I searched the entire newly designed app and can‚Äôt find the followings, which were obvious to users in the old design: 

1st: Deepavali Specials - the items listed under ‚ÄúDeepavali Draw‚Äù in the new design are NOT the same as those advertised in the Straits Times. Previously, they were the same and there was a clear and obvious designed category ‚ÄúDeepavali Specials‚Äù that I could click on to get the full list of items on offer.

2nd: 3-day Weekend Offers: This is not listed at all today in the new design. In the old design of the app, it was uploaded every Friday, to sync with the newspaper advertisement. Plus, users only needed to click ‚Äú3-day Weekend Offers‚Äù to see all items on offer in this category in the old design.

3rd: Brands Offers: The old design was so easy and intuitive to use - just a click on the freebies from the different brands, users would see the various items of that specific brand to buy. Now, users only see the freebie & statement like ‚ÄúFree pan with $60 purchase‚Äù. Click it, users only see the free pan! Now, what users should see is what are the items to choose from to make up $60 to enjoy the free pan.

Can‚Äôt checkout due to address n contact fields errors This is the first time I‚Äôm ordering thru the mobile app and it asked me for my address n contact details. Strange as such details are already stored as I have ordered online many times over the years. Nevertheless I keyed them in but it didn‚Äôt register nor save. I have missed three 2-hrs time slots since morning. For the last one, I had to quickly open my PC n used it to order instead n thankfully it went thru. Please check the bugs in the mobile app. While I would like to thank the workers for their hardwork in this crisis, the service level is still not up to mark. Getting a delivery slot is a full time affair from morning till evening and many items already in the cart are constantly out of stock The whole experience doesn‚Äôt give the assurance that Singapore can feed its people should the pandemic be prolonged.

Room for improvement I have no problem using this App. I am a regular buyer for years from various online grocery Apps namely Redmart, Giant, Sheng Siong, Honestbee and Prime. Though the one disappointing experience is the fresh chicken range is always out of stock 9 out of 10 times when I was going to check out. I wish I could have known it earlier. After spending a long time browsing and finalising my list without the chicken (I usually need to order 4-6 chickens) means I either had to give up my order or order part from here then go to another site to order the chickens.  It‚Äôs also disappointing that there are no fresh pork and seafood.

Delivery Late More Than 2 Hours-Disadvantaging Ppl Delivery is late for more than 2 hours to the promised delivery time. 

Called customer service only to be told to wait for 15-20mins. However when its passed 20mins, every time i called, they give the same instructions to wait for another 15 minutes. In the end i waited for more than 2 hours. 

It is not honest and causes disadvantages to people to tell someone to wait for 15 minutes, only for the delivery to come 2 hour later. I can not go anywhere, if i knows it will be more than 2 hours late, i will finish my other tasks first.

The customer service is not reliable in servicing customer.

The driver on the other hand, called my husband that he will arrive 5-7 minutes. But 20 minutes later, the driver is not here yet. I called the driver, but no explanation is given and it seems like the driver is clueless with the location of our place, despite this is our 3rd time ordering from fairprice online, and my place is just beside mrt.

The driver only arrived 30 minutes later from the promised arrival time. Total waiting time‚Äôs more than 2 hours

Overall not professional, messy logistics, slow response, incompetence, disappointing and not reliable.

Satisfied The app has improved so much since the last time I used. I can find close to all the items I need. Sometimes even those that I don‚Äôt see in every store. The app is updated with weekly PWPs and offers which are found in the stores as well. It is so convenient for me, esp with 2 young kids. I do not need to queue to make payment and carry those heavy and big items home now. Delivery timings can also be selected to make sure you are around when your loot arrives. This is very important if you order frozen and chilled items. Overall, highly satisfied.

The new interface is so so I find it very difficult to choose the products I want when I could not read the details from the selection view. Have to click in to know what item it is. 1) Sale price after discount not shown. Only amount of discount shown so customer have to calculate how much is the final price and if it is worth it. Redmart shows final price upfront! So smart for the shopper to decide!

Legit complaints from a frequent shopper I really hope NTUC succeeds in its foray into the digital space so hear me out here. 

1. Bad UX

- i can search when I‚Äôm not signed in, and when I want to add to my cart I have to sign in which is fair. But when I do, the stuff that I saw that was available is suddenly unavailable. For example, Pampers Premium Care.

- search results are not sorted according to type or relevance! Which is the bare minimum of an e-commerce app. For example, when I search for rice noodles, the first five results are rice noodles or noodles then a trickle of irrelevant products then rice noodles appearing then irrelevant products then rice noodles etc. Why??

- some search results are not relevant! when I search for ‚Äúrice noodles‚Äù I am shown tomato paste, olive oil, canola oil, virgin coconut oil, mustard dressing etc. Why???

- after search results are displayed I have to scroll upwards manually to view starting from top to bottom. Why doesn‚Äôt it display from the top results?

- can you please place all the unavailable items towards the bottom of the search results instead of weaving them intermittently within the available items?

2. Bad fulfilment

The delivery service is really superb. On time, and within the same day of ordering even. However, I refrain from ordering fresh items like chicken or vegetables after a couple times bad experience where I was allocated stale chicken and very old vegetables. To be fair, Sheng Siong and RedMart both do poorly on this category. So should NTUC treat this gap as a major opportunity to outshine your competitors?

3. Bad inventory management

About 50% of the time, my confirmed orders are updated to exclude a couple of items that are not available.

100% of the time, many items that I want to buy aren‚Äôt available. I‚Äôm hard pressed to fill my cart of items worth $79 because so many items are unavailable!
